A classic American diner food without a hint of pretension.

It's a diner.  And a good one, at least for miami.  The staff was friendly and the food was fine.  Plenty of strawberry jam at the tables, which is an issue at many diners. The strawberry is obviously the best, so it gets used up the fastest.  You can gauge the quality of a diner by how much strawberry jam is at the table.  Jimmy's place had plenty.  They care enough to make sure that there was strawberry jelly at each table.  You cannot expect much more than that from a diner.  Also hot sauce. Which they had.
